A formidable symbol of American wilderness, and a hugely popular public attraction in Yellowstone, the grizzly bear would be the biggest animal to come off the endangered species list since the California gray whale was delisted in 1994.
But the recent revival has also sparked conflict with nearby residents as the bears venture out of the national park.
``To say that there is a local agenda against bears is to be paranoid,'' Stokes said, while quickly adding that federal law enforcement officials ``have good reason to be paranoid because nobody likes them around here anyway, and it is their own doing
And the reddish crowns of dying whitebark pines continue to advance across Yellowstone.
